Silica - Sword Art Online

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Silica from Sword Art Online, trained as a LyCORIS network.

One pitfall with this character is that her SAO and ALO outfits share the same design, just with a different color - so they share the same tags during training. This means that SD can sometimes get the color wrong and swap the red and blue outfits. You may have to mess with the prompt/neg prompt a bit to avoid RNG.

Requires extension for use:

https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-lycoris

Recommended tags are:

SAO Outfit: silicabase, brown hair, short twintails, red eyes, armor, pleated skirt, thighhighs, bare shoulders, breastplate, hair ribbon

*Try negative prompting "blue clothing" if you're getting the wrong color

ALO Outfit: silicaalo, brown hair, short twintails, red eyes, cat ears, cat tail, armor, pleated skirt, thighhighs, bare shoulders, breastplate, hair ribbon

*Try negative prompting "red clothing" if you're getting the wrong color

Misc Outfits: dssilica, brown hair, short twintails, red eyes, hair ribbon

I chose not to include "fingerless gloves" as a recommended tag because SD plainly sucks at them...

Check out my HuggingFace repository:

https://huggingface.co/Doctor-Shotgun/ds-LoRA

Check out my Pixiv:

https://www.pixiv.net/en/users/90447503

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate feature but with more flexiblity

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • Lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • Higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris i found out recently that this method actually lower success rate, so only use when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res step at 20, or 1/2 of sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good result without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results to me.

--

Combining with Attribute LoRa / LyCoris

You may need to do your own testing, but using character weight 0.2 below attribute lora weight yields superior results, if for some reason one features persists not showing or overbake, you may want to lower the weight of the overbaked feature Lora, and then use emphasis () to boost the specific attribute you want.

DDetailer Script

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

How to install this script? I kinda forget how because its a bit complicated beacuse you need to install stuff from venv. but a quick google search will land you somewhere in tutorial page.

Please leave a review if you have any critiques or if you find this LoRa good.

WHY LYCORIS?
The ability to adapt cross styles and differentiate each elements of the trained model gives lycoris an edge over conventional LoRa. it can get the same detail with less memories. You can basically morph it into many styles without overfitting into the style of the trained model.

Usage Guide

Lora Weight = 0.1-0.4 (is best for combining, be mindful that your model may contain bias towards specific face such as korean or asian), 0.5-0.7 (is good to retain original face, while not too constraining your prompt), 0.8-1 ( is to generate accurate features of the original person ).

Use Dynamic CFG Threshold

  • Mimic = 10 | Clamp percentile = 99.5

  • Min. Mimic Scale = 0, Cosine Up

  • CFG Scale Sch. = 15, Half Cosine Down

NOTE : I realized that with LyCoris Person, dynamic CFG actually lower success rate. without dynamic CFG result are more highly successful at the cost of a little less detail.

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

Please leave a review if you have any critiques or if you find this LoRa good.
